benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Retrieve account tags

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01 (happy path), @TC06, @TC07, @TC08, @TC09, @TC10, @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC20, @TC21, @TC22, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25 cover successful retrieval, invalid account IDs, non-existent accounts, and various query parameters.
Empty Response: @TC06 covers accounts with no tags.
Query Parameters: Multiple scenarios (@TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC09, @TC10, @TC15, @TC19, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25) test inclusion of deleted tags, audit levels, extra parameters, and edge cases.
Error Handling: @TC07, @TC08, @TC09, @TC14, @TC15, @TC20, @TC21, @TC22, @TC23, @TC24 cover invalid account IDs, unsupported parameters, and malformed inputs.
Performance & Load: @TC16 (large number of tags), @TC17 (concurrent requests) address performance testing.
Regression & Compatibility: @TC18, @TC19 ensure previously fixed issues and backward compatibility.
gaps: Pagination: No tests explicitly verify pagination handling for large datasets beyond the single large dataset scenario in @TC16.
Authorization: No explicit tests for missing or invalid authentication tokens (@TC12, @TC13) are included, though some are implied.
Rate Limiting: No tests cover rate limiting or throttling behavior.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for pagination to verify correct handling of paged responses with large datasets.
Include tests for missing or invalid authentication tokens to ensure proper authorization handling.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system robustness under load.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
